The paper focuses on video object segmentation in a human-robot interaction setting, which falls under the robotics (cs.RO) category. The proposed method involves deep learning techniques for appearance and motion analysis, which is a common theme in computer vision (cs.CV) research. The use of a teacher-student learning paradigm and incremental learning also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the importance of human-robot interaction and the use of a carefully designed dataset, which suggests a focus on human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
